oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Wagonload of hay
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph shows a wagonload of hay taken from .4 acres of land that had been treated with #120 triple super phosphate. There is an unidentified man and a boy with the wagon which is being pulled by a horse and a mule.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Carts & wagons; Hay; Horses; Mules; Farms
